args:
When tears leading to the otherworld start
to repeatedly appear, the group realizes the
cause is Alfonse and his allies, causing them to
search even harder for a way home. In pursuit
of clues, the group makes its way to a secret
Empire laboratory.
After Alfonse and his allies help protect the town,\nsome time passes.
Back in the Halidom, Alfonse and the others\ncontinue searching for a way home. However...
Welcome back, Prince Alfonse. ...Uh oh.\nJudging from the look on your face,\nI'm guessing things didn't go well.

Well, I suppose such is wont to happen
more times than not; locating a new means
to move from one world to another is no
mean feat.
Indeed. If we could freely open such paths\nas you can in your world, this would be far\nless troubling.
I've been digging through old tomes in an\nattempt to find a solution to our problem,\nbut the results have been less than stellar.
I'm sorry. I wish we could be more help.

Don't help that the Empire's been even
more active than usual lately. Every time
those chumps pop up, it takes time away
from lookin' for yer home.

You have provided more than able
assistance. Why, it's only thanks to
you that we've been able to focus
on our objective at all.
It's possible that the Dyrenell Empire's\nincreased activity of late is somehow\ntied into Loki's presence.
It seems our problems have become yours.
Any friend of the Empire is an enemy of\nours, so we'll just take her out with the\nrest of the trash!
Well, I thank you for your enthusiasm.
Pardon my changing of the subject,\nbut there is a matter I wish to discuss.
As we made our way back, a rip in space\nsuddenly appeared and disgorged a good\namount of black mana.
These tears occur in the border between\nthis world and the beyond. They lead to\na place called ＂the space between worlds.＂
Then this ＂space between worlds＂ serves\nas a sort of nexus between one world\nand the next? Interesting...
I wonder... Were we to pass through\nthat place, might it take us home?
If you'd like to die, feel free to try it.
Do you know something of this?
No. But I DO know none of you can\nsurvive the power that sleeps there.
Not that I care what happens to you.
Veronica is correct—if a bit harsh.\nThe space between worlds is a profoundly\nwarped area of existence.
Merely stepping into it is enough to snuff\nout the life of an average person.
And the rifts needed to enter it aren't\nexactly common.
Can you tell us more about what you saw?\nWhat happened to it?
It disappeared almost as quickly as it\narrived. It seems I was right to think it\nfar from an ordinary phenomenon...
Yes, this is certainly something\nwe should start looking into.
Forgive me, Your Highness, but I've an\nurgent report of a rip in space suddenly\nappearing in a nearby village!
And there are a crapload of fiends spillin'\nout of it! Like, a METRIC crapload!
We will accompany you. Let us be off!
...That really is a tear into the otherworld.\nBut why is it appearing HERE?

Guys, I don't wanna be a nag or whatever,
but maaaaaybe we should think about
plugging the stupid hole all these fiends
keep coming out of?
If you know of a way to close it, Notte,\nI am more than willing to liste...
It...closed up?! What's going on here...?
This is not normal behavior for\nsuch an object?
Not really, no. I mean, these rips are\ninherently unstable, but to have one just\nwink out like that is...unusual.
Eh, who cares! Problem solved for now,\nam I right?
Dammit! We got more fiends incomin'!\nEverybody grab a weapon and...
...Okay, now THAT one closed up?\nSomebody find an egghead to tell me\nwhat in the fresh hell is goin' on here!
Didn't I tell you that things were about\nto get much more fun?
Meee? Oh my good heavens, no.\nThis is YOUR doing!
Enough of your blasted riddles, Loki!
*sigh* Oh, very well. The cause of this\nabnormality is YOU, Prince Alfonse.\nOh, and Princess Veronica.
Unlike the world you come from,\nthis one is rather...unstable.

And it seems that the combined effect of
the Askran power to open gates, and the
Emblian power to close them, has sent
it reeling.
Then WE are the cause of these rifts?
Did I not just make that perfectly clear?\nGoodness, but you ARE dense sometimes.
Yes, I'm sure it's a bitter pill to swallow\nfor a sweet, naive thing like yourself.
But don't worry, dear. I've come with a plan\nto make everything neat as a pin again!
The solution is exceptionally simple:\nEither the power of Askr OR the power of\nEmbla must disappear from this world.
Askr and Embla are two sides of a coin.\nIf only one is present, the power stops.
Maybe that outfit is cutting off the blood\nto your brain, but we've been trying to\nsend them home this entire time!
Have you considering killing one of them?\nThat would solve the problem nicely.
Oh, and if you decide to do that,\nplease make sure I'm invited.\nI DO love a good show!
But until then, have fun in this chaotic\nhellscape of a world you created. Byeee!
Man, I am SO tired of that lady!\nI'm gonna find her and... Uh oh! Fiends!
It's another rip in space! Come on!
Such chaos... Such misery...\nAnd all because of me.
I'm heading for the rip that just appeared\nin Niege Village. Elisanne, take a group\nwith you and head to Fuyar.
No, I'll go! Your knowledge will be needed\nto seek out a way for us to return home!
Can't wait to see ya in action!
We must return to our own world before\nthis one is torn apart... But HOW?
That one of us kills the other?\nNo! Out of the question!
It doesn't matter to me,\nsince you'll be the one dying.
Is there truly no other way to resolve\nthe problem save by battle?
No one is killing anyone today.\nWe'll find another way.
You have a truce in this world, remember?
And yet we are creating untold misery\nfor everyone in this place.
As a prince of your people, is your first\nresponsibility not to them?
The Alberia I hope to build is one where\nno life is traded away or sacrificed.
If I let one of you kill the other, I'd never\nbe able to hold that up as an ideal again.
Ideals are essential to build a just nation,\nand I will not see either of you sacrificed.
You are a strong one indeed.
It makes more sense to just\nkill everyone in your way.
If I did that, I would be no better\nthan the wicked demon himself.
A thousand years ago, a terrible evil\nattacked this world and... Wait. That's it!
During the era when humans and dragons\nwarred with each other, the humans found\na novel way to battle their enemy.
They created a kind of portal called the\nUncanny Gate and used it to summon\nforth a wicked demon from another world.
They CREATED a path to another world?!

The demon was eventually sealed away,
but three hundred years ago, the Dyrenell
Empire began an investigation into how
to open the gate in an attempt to revive it.
Then they would have the knowledge\nof how to create such a gate?
It's certainly possible, which means we\nshould go investigate as soon as we can!
